\section{Value}{

Each port is a flexible method for assigning a value parameter or variable.
The current value of the parameter
or variable has a location on some object or module object, and it is
always retrieved from that location:

\code{xds_obj$...$value}
}

\section{Functional Response}{

The value of the parameter is set by a function call with
a standard form:

\code{xds_obj <- this_case_port(t, xds_obj)}

where \code{t} is time.
The \code{xds_obj} is passed, modified, and returned.

Inside \code{this_case_port} functions can use
any variables that have been defined. The
value is set by a function call:

\code{xds_obj$...$value <- F_this_case(t, vars)}

where \code{F_this_case} is an \code{S3} object
that dispatches on \code{class(value)}.
}

\section{Default Case}{

The default case for \code{F_this_case} is a pair of methods that set
a constant value for the parameter:
\itemize{
\item \code{this_case_port.setup}
\itemize{
\item assigns a static value to \code{xds_obj$...$value}
\item sets \code{class(xds_obj$...$value) =  "static"}
}
\item \code{this_case_port.static} returns \code{xds_obj} unmodified
}
}

\section{Trace Case}{

